	   <tr><td colspan=2>Its very probable that VI actually researches these boards to get customer feedback on new items in the game. That being the case, this post is specifically designed for VI eyes.<br>In regards to the bash skill, it does indeed require a shield for Paladins and SKs (unless you're an ogre I think). Anyway, if it doesn't already exist, have you considered a shield with a random proc? Granted, stun requires a save roll, so adding a bash-triggered proc to a shield would require an additional save roll. Maybe thats out of the question. It would be a unique feature to an epic-style shield though. <br>I wouldn't think that class balancing would be an issue at levels required to obtain such an item. But it would be nice to have a shield that could random a stackable self-only hp buff, or a party buff for that matter. <br>Don't get me wrong - clickable is nice, but randomed would add an entirely new dimension to the bash skill.<br>Not to mention that it would be a highly sought after item that would maximize the utility of your customers and thereby generate revenue during a time of slow-down in the American and world-wide economy. Adding an item such as this to your 'matrix' would almost certainly be a pivotal point in the upward mobility of VI as a viable software producing company. Perhaps similar concepts have never made it out of the boardroom, but I think you know its time has come.<br><br>PS - no one is stopping you from putting a random proc on warrior-only bracers either (also used to bash). I'll give you a moment to clean the milk out of your nose...<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
